    <abstract id="aspace_d2f14745cdf0279cbff6275a086f311c">Joseph A. Goney served as an officer in several labor organizations, including the Steel Workers Organizing Committee, United Steelworkers of America, Association of Catholic Trade Unionists, the Allegheny County CIO Political Action Committee and Steel City Industrial Union Council.  This collection contains correspondence and newspaper clippings documenting Pittsburgh area labor history, particularly the 1937 strike by SWOC Local 1601 at Heppenstall Steel Company.  Photographs of USWA events are also included.</abstract>
